├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│   Virtualization Layer               │
│   • Logical qubit abstraction        │
│   • Topology masking                │
│   • Fault injection/testing         │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│   Hardware Interface Layer           │
│   • Qubit control pulses            │
│   • Cryo system monitoring          │
│   • Calibration routines            │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

6.2 Hybrid Algorithm Frameworks

6.2.1 Variational Quantum Algorithms (VQAs)

· Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm (QAOA): For combinatorial problems
· Variational Quantum Eigensolver (VQE): For quantum chemistry
· 6G Application: Real-time network optimization with changing conditions

6.2.2 Quantum Machine Learning

· Quantum Neural Networks: Parameterized quantum circuits as ML models
· Quantum Kernel Methods: Exponential feature space advantages
· Federated Quantum Learning: Distributed QML across 6G network

6.2.3 Quantum Digital Twins

· Real-time quantum simulations of physical systems
· 6G Integration: Sensor data continuously updates the quantum model
· Applications: City-scale traffic, protein folding, climate modeling

6.3 Development Tools & Environments

· Quantum CI/CD: Testing on quantum simulators before QPU deployment
· Noise Modeling & Mitigation: Software tools for error characterization
· Cross-Platform Abstraction: Write once, run on any QPU architecture

