8. Commercial & Server-Scale Implementation

8.1 Facility Design Requirements

8.1.1 Quantum Data Center Specifications

· Vibration Isolation: <10 nm displacement from ground motion
· Electromagnetic Shielding: <1 pT magnetic field variation
· Thermal Stability: ±0.001°C in QPU chamber
· Power Stability: Uninterruptible with superconducting magnetic energy storage
· Network Connectivity: Multiple diverse 6G/optical paths

8.1.2 Modular Deployment Strategies

```
City-Wide Quantum Computing Infrastructure:
┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐
│  Central    │    │  Edge       │    │  Edge       │
│  Quantum    │◄──►│  Quantum    │◄──►│  Quantum    │
│  Hub        │    │  Node       │    │  Node       │
│  (1000+ LQ) │    │  (10-50 LQ) │    │  (10-50 LQ) │
└─────────────┘    └─────────────┘    └─────────────┘
        ▲                  ▲                  ▲
        │                  │                  │
┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐
│  6G Core    │    │  6G Edge    │    │  6G Edge    │
│  Network    │    │  Cloud      │    │  Cloud      │
└─────────────┘    └─────────────┘    └─────────────┘
```

8.2 Business Models & Access Frameworks

8.2.1 Quantum-as-a-Service (QaaS) Tiers:

· Tier 1 (Education/Development): Simulator access, small QPU time slots
· Tier 2 (Enterprise): Dedicated logical qubits, hybrid algorithm support
· Tier 3 (Government/Research): Full stack access, custom algorithm development
· Tier 4 (Strategic Partnership): Co-design of QPU architectures

8.2.2 Pricing Models:

· Quantum Volume Hours: Based on computational power (logical qubits × coherence time)
· Entanglement-as-a-Service: Per Bell pair generated
· Algorithm-Specific Pricing: Fixed price for solving particular problem types
· Subscription Models: Monthly access to quantum processing units

